### Register a new user
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "student1@example.com",
    "password": "securepassword123"
}

###

### Login to get JWT Token
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "student1@example.com",
    "password": "securepassword123"
}

###

### Save Token Variable (Requires REST Client extension)
@authToken = {{login.response.body.access_token}}

###

### Get User Profile (using token)
# Replace id with the actual user ID returned from login/register if needed
GET http://localhost:3000/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### Get All Subjects (Public Authenticated Route)
GET http://localhost:3000/learning/subjects
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

###

### Admin: Create a Subject (WILL FAIL if user is not ADMIN)
POST http://localhost:3000/learning/subjects
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Mathematics",
    "description": "Core mathematics lessons"
}
